Luvuyo Memela celebrates with Augustine Mulenga and Xola Mlambo of Orlando Pirates during the 2019 Carling Black Label Cup. JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates have terminated the contracts of eight first-team players, including midfielder Xola Mlambo and Zambia striker Augustine Mulenga. After finishing in third place in the 2019/20 campaign, the Buccaneers are streamlining their squad. READ: PSL announces DStv as new league sponsor Mulenga, Mlambo and veteran defender Alfred Ndegane are the most high-profile departures. This happens as coach Josef Zinnbauer looks to build a squad to challenge for the inaugural DStv Premiership campaign.